      • createSubscription

        public void createSubscription(Map<String,Object> params,
                      ISirqulCallback<WrappedResponse<SubscriptionResponse>> callback)
        Create a subscription for a billable entity. Provide a planId, if not provided then the base plan will be assigned.

        Target API Endpoint: /subscription/create

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          The account used to perform the create, must be the responsible manager
        • SirqulKeys.planId
          The plan to subscribe to, if null use default plan
        • SirqulKeys.promoCode
          Set a promo code for a discount.

        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        a WrappedResponse<SubscriptionResponse> on a valid response, SirqulResponse on an invalid response
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred. Each of these cases are broken up into separate interface methods. If you foresee yourself needing to handle all cases, it's recommended you simply instantiate a new ISirqulCallback instance, which will force you to implement all methods. If you really only care about one or a few of them, you can use the SirqulCallback class, which you can optionally override any of those same interface methods. If you wish to ignore any response, simply pass in null for this.
        See Also:
        SubscriptionObject.createSubscription

        public void deleteSubscription(Map<String,Object> params,
                      ISirqulCallback<SirqulResponse> callback)
        Suspend the current subscription for the billable entity managed by the account. The account must be the responsible manager to perform this action.

        Target API Endpoint: /subscription/delete

        Available parameters for this api

          The account used to perform the delete, must be the responsible manager

      • getSubscriptionPlans

        public void getSubscriptionPlans(Map<String,Object> params,
                        ISirqulCallback<WrappedResponse<List<SubscriptionPlanResponse>>> callback)
        Get the list of available subscription plans. Plans are a default set of subscription options.

        Target API Endpoint: /subscription/plan/list

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.visible
          Include visible only (true), hidden only (false), or all (null)
        • SirqulKeys.role
          The role the plan is targeted for, values are: DEVELOPER, RETAILER, ADVERTISER
